In a message dated 5/25/03 9:27:51 AM, jrivers(-at-)globalserve.net writes:

<< I guess I should have worried about heat,,, as the paint pealed the first

time it was parked in  the direct sun in the summer. >>

If it was a brand name exterior paint, this shouldn't have happened even
with the heat...A light sanding and brushing/vacuuming is good prep for
repainting existing paint. Try Will-Bond or another brand of "liquid sand-
paper" for hard to reach spots and even all over for giving the surface
"tooth" to help the new paint bond to the old...

